The paper deals with the analysis and modeling of plant roots, which involves image processing and statistical analysis. This suggests that the paper could belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) or machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper involves the representation of root structures as points in a tree-shape space, which suggests that it could also belong to the graph theory (cs.GR) or computational geometry (cs.CG) sub-categories. The paper also discusses the use of the framework in various applications, including classification and symmetry analysis, which suggests that it could belong to the signal and image processing (cs.SI) or bioinformatics (cs.BIO) sub-categories.
